   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>To the secretary of the village of Bacchias, from Diogenes, son of Limnaios, of the village of Karanis. In accordance with the orders issued I declare the 14 1/2 arourai of a catoecic allotment belonging to me near the village of Bacchias, which are under lien for unpaid taxes in the name of Petheus, son of Hatres, and are registered for payment of taxes in the name of . . ., as unwatered for the present 11th year of Aurelius Antoninus Caesar the lord, Armeniacus Medicus Parthicus Maximus.</ab>
         </div>
